        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:54PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles north of Sherman Pass, or 52 miles northeast of Omak. This
storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central Ferry
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
